reviewText: Raven VS PJ Polaco: The match was alright. The more I watched TNA PPVS of 2005, the more I like Raven.Team Canada vs. 3LK: I could really careless for either team.Jeff Hardy vs. Monty Brown: Both Hardy and Brown's TNA careers didnt pan out to well. An alright match but didnt get me to excited.Christopher Daniels, Samoa Joe, Alex Shelley, and Roderick Strong vs. Chris Sabin, Sonjay Dutt, Matt Bently, and Austin Aries: Match of the night. Action was nonstop but towards the ends the pins came fast and weighed down the match a bit. Probably a poke at WWE considering this was November and it was an elimination match. Survivor Series for fans who didnt get it.Sabu vs. Abyss: Match was alright. They really didnt show off any moves I havent seen either do in there careers. The ending of the match was brutal.AJ Styles vs. Petey Williams: Never seen these two have a bad match and its not going start here.Team 3-D and Rhino vs. Jeff Jarrett and AMW: The match wasnt anything speical. The camera crew had a tough time trying to catch all the action going on. Rhino's underwear hangs out during most of the match. A few spots that could have been really cool but they stopped them from doing so. Christian then comes in and joins the babyfaces.Chrisitan also made his first TNA apperance on this show. Of course to get over with fans he had to say WWE was stale and boring. I like Christian but if he couldnt do an interview, he wouldnt be where he is today.A good card overall, with the X-divison once again taking center stage. Its neat how 2005 started off like WCW with Hall, Nash, Jarrett, DDP, among others trying to revive there careers. By the end of 2005, DDP and Hall would be gone. Samoa Joe, Team 3-D, Christian and a slew of other wrestlers would enter TNA.

reviewText: Just like WWE usually has a great follow up PPV to WrestleMania called Backlash, TNA was able to do the same thing with their Genesis PPV.  I liked Bound For Glory better but this was a nice follow up.  This also happened the same day as Eddie Guerrero's death so there are references to him by Konnan & Team 3D throughout the show.Pre-Show: Shark Boy vs. Nigel McGinness - Honestly, nothing special here to remember.Pre-Show: The Naturals & Lance Hoyt vs. Diamonds In The Rough - Nice six man tag match.Raven vs. PJ Polaco a.k.a. Justin Credible - This wasn't exactly an ECW style brawl like we've seen before but there was some great storytelling here by Raven.Hockey Stick Fight w/Kip James as referee: Team Canada vs. 3 Live Kru - Fun match to watch.Christian Cage makes his TNA debut & shoots on the WWE - Basically, Christian makes his debut only a few days (Taboo Tuesday was earlier in the week) after leaving WWE to address all the rumors regarding his contract situation and basically says what alot of the former WWE fans have been saying about their product for the past couple of months.Jeff Hardy vs. "Alpha Male" Monty Brown - Not a wild brawl but better than I expected.Elimation X Match: Christopher Daniels, Samoa Joe, Alex Shelly, Roderick Strong vs. Chris Sabin, Matt Bentley, Sonjay Dutt, Austin Aries - Great Survivor Series type battle between these eight with alot of the famous high spots & actual wrestling by each wrestler.  However, the aftermath with Samoa Joe & Christopher Daniels is more memorable than anything else.No DQ Match: Sabu vs. Abyss - Not on the same level as their involvement in Monster's Ball but it's still a nice brawl between the two.  Not many weapons used but it served it's purpose.X Division Champion AJ Styles vs. Petey Williams - This match heavily makes up for their match a year earlier between the two at Victory Road (same match on "Best Of The X Division" DVD).Rhino/Team 3D a.k.a. Dudley Boyz vs. Jeff Jarrett/America's Most Wanted - This match resemembles an old school ECW style brawl with them brawling all over the building in this one.  A great & wild six man tag match.The DVD extras are basically just backstage footage of wrestlers before & after their matches.Again, I recommend but I would get Bound For Glory first.
summary: Nice Follow Up To Bound For Glory

reviewText: This was an awesome PPV from TNA. TNA has just been on a roll with PPV's ever since they started doing 3 hour shows. Bellow is the card with a Five Star Rating System.PRESHOW: SHARK BOY vs. NIGEL MCGUINNESSThis match was the opener before the PPV. It might be on the DVD since TNA are now adding the pre-shows as extras which is a good idea. It was your typical match from what I remember. They have had better openers. *1/2PRESHOW: THE DIAMONDS IN THE ROUGH vs. THE NATURALS & LANCE HOYTThis was a good match featuring the return of Chase Stevens from The Naturals. Stevens had suffered a broken neck weeks before. This was better then the following match and got the crowd going for the PPV. Orlando loves Lance Hoyt. **1/2RAVEN vs. ???This opening match on the show featured Raven takeing on an mystery opponent appointed my Larry Z. I wont ruin who it is, but this was a good match. Not horrible, but not amazing. It serves its purpose. **3/4HOCKEY STICK FIGHT:TEAM CANADA vs. 3LIVE KRU(Special Referee: Kip James)This was a pretty entertaining match. Eric Young is funny as hell in this contest. The purpose of the match was to even the odds since there was four Canadians and three of the Kru. Kip James is added in the ongoing story of "who can you trust?" One of the better matches that these two teams have put on. ***Christian Cage Debuts.This was the major acquisition and let me tell you it did not disappoint. I was glad to see a man who has been given the shaft as a single star jump. Christian has an unbelieveable amount of charisma and is an awesome wrestler. This is about 10-20 minute shoot segement which sets up the main event later in the night. *****CONTENDER'S MATCH:"THE ALPHA MALE" MONTY BROWN vs. "THE CHARISMATIC ENIGMA" JEFF HARDYThis was better than I thought it was going to be. I just don't understand why the winner never got the shot they deserve. But it was a good showing from both men. ***ELIMINATION X:"THE FALLEN ANGEL" CHRISTOPHER DANIELS, "THE SAMOAN SUBMISSION MACHINE" SAMOA JOE, ALEX SHELLEY, & RODERICK STRONG vs. CHRIS SABIN, MATT BENTLEY, SONJAY DUTT, & AUSTIN ARIESTNA's answer to the Survivor Series. This was a fantastic match that had a few surprise's thrown into it. I was very glad this match was given about 30 minutes as all of these men deserve that kind of time limit. *****NO DISQUALIFICATION MATCH:SABU VS. "THE MONSTER" ABYSSI was surprised to see these two men compete in another hardcore type match, just coming off the Bound For Glory Monster's Ball. It was a brutal match that set's up the Final Encounter at Turning Point. That PPV is a must buy also. Sick bumps that both men take, more so Sabu. *****TNA X-DIVISION TITLE MATCH:"THE PHENOMENAL" AJ STYLES (c) vs. "THE CANADIAN DESTROYER" PETEY WILLIAMSTne only title match of the night. Which was a good thing and bad thing. This was better then the last title match these two put on from Victory Road one year ago. This time AJ was champ and both men are extremely hard workers. This is what WWE wishes there "crusier weight division" was. Just an awesome match. *****MAIN EVENT:TEAM 3D & RHINO vs. NWA WORLD HEAVYWEIGHT CHAMPION, JEFF JARRETT & NWA WORLD TAG TEAM CHAMPIONS, AMERICA'S MOST WANTEDBefore the match took place, Team 3D and Rhino cut a promo backstage. The best part is the fact that all three pay tribute Eddie, since he passed away early in the day. R.I.P. Eddie.The match was just a brawl all over the building and was not really a six man tag match. It was a good main event and was better then the last six man tag match that was supposed to be the main event that featured: Nash, Hall and Jarrett vs. Hardy Styles and Macho Man from the previous Turning Point. This match made me forget all about that one. *****After the match Christian came back out as it was time to choose. TNA or Team Jarrett. Im sure by know everyone knows what happened. So Jarrett recieves a 3D through the table at the hands of the Dud....I mean Team 3D and Christian.A great show that keeps TNA PPV record going. The extras are the pre-show at the begining of the PPV and never before seen backstage footage. Plus what happened when Genesis went off the air. Deff a must buy as almost every match was awesome.

reviewText: Team Canada v 3liveKru Hockey Stick Fight: I don't remember this one much but I think Kip James was ref. Either that or it's when Konnan turnt on the 3live Crew.Monty Brown v Jeff Hardy Contenders Match :This was one of Hardy's last matches on a ppv, who knows if he will be back since he only shows when he feels like it. Anyway when Hardy was showing up he had some of the best matches and was still heald back by Jarrett. I guess I don't blame them for not giving him a world title push since he's not the most dedicated wrestler to the business. Even Monty Brown is more dedicated than him and I guess the right person won since I'm the biggest fan of the Pounce. Yep, you guessed it, Monty wins with the Pounce and it's awhile before he even gets another title shot eventhough he won. They shouldn't have put Hardy's face all over the posters if he was gonna just be jobbing in a mid-card match.*** out of ****Samoa Joe, Christopher Daniels, Alex Shelley + Roderick Strong v Chris Sabin, Austin Aries, Matt Bentley + Sonjay Dutt Elimination XAbyss v Sabu No Disqualification: It's not a bad survivor series type match with Danials and Joe winning. Joe goes nuts because he doesn't make the final pin and beats the crap out of Danials.*** 1/2 out of ****AJ Styles v Petey Williams X Division Title::This of course was an excellent match with the under-rated Petey Williams giving it all against A.J. Styles. Before this match on Impact Petey beat A.J. in a non-title match but he loses with one to the styles clash i think.**** out of ****Jeff Jarrett + America's Most Wanted v Rhino + Team 3D : Team 3-D mess up AMW in this one and almost injured one of them. They get the win with the 3-D while Jarrett and Rhino fight outside. It's not a bad match with a lot of brawling but not really mainevent worthy. What helps the match some is Christians appearance at the end where he beats up Jarrett and turns on Team Canada. *** out of **** Was nice seeing Christian debut but since it was the day Eddie Guerrero died that was about all that was really on my mind.
summary: Another one that's not the best example of a great TNA ppv

reviewText: The preshow for TNA's Genesis starts up, with Shane Douglas and Jeremy Borash running down the card and hyping the major star coming to TNA at Genesis.-Shark Boy vs. Nigel McGuinness: Decent opening match, quick one though. Nigel mocks Shark Boy after hitting some nice moves and starts working on his arm. Nice headstand into a back kick by Nigel and a hammerlock into a DDT on Shark Boy. Then Shark Boy fights back, with punches and a bulldog from the second rope. Nice suplex from the top by Nigel. The finish comes when Shark Boy gets a roll up on Nigel for the win in about 6 minutes. 5/10.-Team Canada segment hyping the six sided hockey stick and the X-Division Championship matches on the PPV tonight.-Diamonds in the Rough vs. The Naturals & Lance Hoyt: Not a bad one here, Elix Skipper starts out taking down Hoyt with punches and a nice back kick. Hoyt comes back with a one armed overhead slam and punches in the corner. Nice flip by Andy Douglas onto David Young and Skipper over the top rope on the outside, followed by a splash over the ropes by Hoyt.The Diamonds take over, with Skipper exploiting Chase Stevens injured head. Hoyt gets the tag, hits a nice dropkick then a double chokeslam on Young and Skipper. The finish comes when Skipper and Young hit a double face buster on Stevens for the win in about 6 minutes. 6/10.-The PPV starts with a tribute to Eddie Guerrero who passed away early that day.-Now a great video package hyping the main events of Genesis.-Live in the Impact Zone, there are some Eddie chants then we start with our first match.-Raven vs. PJ Polaco: The former Justin Credible puts on an okay show here, it's a decent match just not very good. Polaco uses some submission holds and knees to the back. Raven gets a break when Cassidy Riley comes in and takes a cane shot to the head. Raven comes back hitting a couple of clotheslines then an ankle lock. Polaco fights out of it and hits a bad looking DDT. The finish comes when Raven hits the Raven Effect DDT for the win in about 6 minutes. 5/10.-Six Sided Hockey Stick Match: 3 Live Kru vs. Team Canada w/ Special Referee Kip James: Nice Eddie tribute by Konnan before the match, followed by Eddie chants from the crowd. The idea is you must be the legal man to grab a hockey stick and use it. The match isn't really that good, though the stuff with Kip James and Eric Young was funny. Nice move by Konnan throwing his sneaker at Young's chest, looked like it hurt. All six men keep trying to go for the hockey sticks, but are stopped from using them. The match breaks down as all six men brawl and the finish comes when Konnan and B.G. hold a hockey stick over the stomach and other areas of Young as The Truth hits a leg drop off the top rope for the win. 5/10.-Next a nice promo by James Mitchell telling Sabu what will happen to him when he gets in the ring with Abyss, cool segment.-Next the debut of Christian Cage: Huge, I mean huge pop from the crowd. Great promo by Cage as he runs down WWE, but mostly praises TNA. Coach D'Amore of Team Canada comes down with Bobby Roode and tries to get Cage to join them, he even hands Cage a Team Canada t-shirt. Cage says it looks like the right size, but he'll need some time to see if it's the right fit. 10/10 for the segment.-Contender's Match: Monty Brown vs. Jeff Hardy: Great promo before the match by Brown, pretty funny. The match itself is not that bad, but not that good. Hardy's mocking of Brown was funny, early on in the match. Brown uses plenty of power moves and Hardy uses his high flying moves to try and win. Hardy tight rope walks part of the Impact Zone and hits a clothesline on Brown. Brown takes over for a bit, but Hardy fights back and hits a Twist of Fate and goes for the Swanton, but misses. The finish comes when Brown hits the Pounce for the win in about 9 minutes. 6/10.-Elimination X: Christopher Daniels, Samoa Joe, Alex Shelley & Roderick Strong vs. Chris Sabin, Sonjay Dutt, Austin Aries & Matt Bentley: Done WWE "Survivor Series" style, once your pinned or submit your eliminated and the match goes until all four members of one team is eliminated. The match is great, plenty of high flying moves by everyone, except Shelley who uses nice submission moves and Joe who hits plenty of power moves. I love the trio of moves by Joe, an inverted atomic drop, a diving front kick and a senton splash. Loved the triple dives by Aries, Dutt and Sabin onto the outside. No one is eliminated until about 12 minutes into the match, when Aries hits a 450 splash off the top onto Strong for the pin, then Aries is rolled up by Daniels about 25 seconds after that. Dutt hits a nice arm drag on on Shelley while also hitting a hurricarana on Daniels from the top rope. Shelly then gets Dutt in a crossface hold and Dutt taps out. Soon after Bentley hits a superkick on Shelley for the pin. Great tower of doom, with Joe hitting a powerbomb while Bentley and Sabin superplex Daniels. Bentley gets up on Daniels shoulders, then Joe slaps him and hits the Musclebuster and Kokina Clutch on Bentley for the tap out. Sabin is the only one left, but he makes the most of it and almost eliminates both Daniels and Joe on several occasions. Joe has Sabin in the Musclebuster, but Bentley pulls Joe to the outside, then Daniels hits the Angels Wings for the pin in about 23 minutes. 11/10. Great postmatch stuff with Joe brutally beating Daniels and busting him open, with a chair and a facewash kick into the steel guard rail. Then he hits a Musclebuster on Daniels, Joe then grabs a chair and hits another Musclebuster on the chair. AJ even comes out after this to see if Daniels is okay, which leads to a match at the following PPV, Turning Point.-No DQ Match: Sabu vs. Abyss: Sabu teases having barbwire on his arm to psych out Abyss. Good match actually, Sabu uses the chair a lot and hits some splashes on the outside onto Abyss, including a leg drop splash onto Abyss through a table. Abyss uses plenty of power moves and even appears to break Sabu's nose. Abyss has a bag of thumbtacks, while Sabu has a chair wrapped in barbwire, but James Mitchell stops Sabu from using the chair. Abyss chokeslams Sabu onto the pile of tacks, and a lot of tacks stick into his back. Abyss goes for the pin, but Sabu kicks out, then Abyss goes for a splash and lands right on the tacks. Sabu goes for the Camel Clutch but Abyss grabs the rope. The finish comes when Abyss hits the Black Hole Slam onto the barbwire chair for the win in about 10 minutes. 8/10.-X-Division Championship: AJ Styles (Champion) vs. Petey Williams: Nice promo from AJ, talking about this match, but also what Joe did to Daniels earlier. This one was much, much better than their match at Victory Road the year before. Great moves by both men, great flip dive by AJ onto Williams on the outside, and AJ goes into the crowd over the guard rail as he does the dive. Williams hits a vicious german suplex on AJ on the outside slamming AJ into the guard rail. Williams starts working on AJ's back and chest, with kicks and submission moves. AJ comes back and hits the pele kick and a nice hurricarana. More back and forth moves by both men, then Williams lock on a Sharpshooter, but AJ gets to the ropes, then hits a springboard forearm shot on Williams. The finish comes when AJ hits the Styles Clash on Williams from the second rope as Joe looks on from the stage for the win in about 18 minutes. 10/10.-Next a promo from Rhino and Team 3D, hyping the six man revenge main event up next. All three men do a nice tribute to Eddie Guerrero to end the segment.-Six Man Revenge Match: Jeff Jarrett & America's Most Wanted vs. Rhino & Team 3D: Great brawl by all six men, very much like the old ECW and a lot closer than anything WWE has tried to do with WWECW. The match starts out in the crowd and stays there for a few minutes and there's plenty of hardcore action from all six men. Brother Devon brawls with Harris and Ray brawls with Storm. Rhino uses a garbage can on Jarrett and press slams him onto a chair. Jarrett does Irish Whip Rhino into a bunch of chairs. Rhino tries to gore Jarrett through a table set up at the entrance way, but Storm stops it. Devon busts open Harris and Ray busts open Storm using a cheese grater. The brawling continues and eventually the match gets back into the ring. The table comes into play, but AMW stops it from being used on several occasions. AMW and Jarrett do take over for a while. The finish comes when Team 3D hits the 3D on Storm for the win in about 15 minutes. 11/10. Post match has Jarrett, AMW and Team Canada attack all three men, until Cage comes down and looks like he's coming in for the save. But he takes off his jacket to reveal the Team Canada t-shirt, but he then hits the Unprettier on Coach D'AMore, then throws Jarrett off the top rope. Cage then hits a 3D on Jarrett through the table with both members of Team 3D lifting up Jarrett for Cage. Great finish for a great PPV.The extras include numerous backstage footage of TNA stars before they make their ways to the ring. The best one though is after the PPV went off the air, when Cage, Rhino and Team 3D pay tribute to Eddie, bring a fan into the ring (I think Devon's daughter) and praise TNA. Cage finishes by saying he will become NWA champion. Great segment, 10/10.One of the best PPV's I've seen in a long time despite the few dud matches.
Title: N/A

reviewText: The Raven-PJ Polaco match was not great but pretty good. The 3Live Kru-Team Canada-Hockey Stick Fight was passable. The Monty Brown-Jeff Hardy match was so-so. The Elimination X match was high-flying,hard-hitting and a good reminder of WWE's Survivor Series matches when they were good. The Abyss-Sabu-NO DQ match was a good reminder of the 1990's ECW. The X Division title match between AJ Styles & Petey Williams was your basic high-flying,back-and-forth showstealer. The 6 man tag team match between The Team of Rhino & Team 3D against Jeff Jarrett & America's Most Wanted was a smash-mouth,hard-hitting,hardcore brawl. I give this event a 7 out of 10.

VERY ENTERTAINING MATCH, AND EVEN BETTER WITH CHRISTIAN CAGE COMING OUT WITH A TEAM CANADA SHIRT, BUT TURNED ON PLANET JARRET AND PLANTED SCOTT D'AMORE TROUGH A TABLE WITH THE 3D! AWESOME!WINNERS: TEAM 3D & RHINORATING: 9OVERALL, GENESIS 2005 WAS WORTH 8 OUT OF 10 STARS. ANOTHER AWESOME PAY PER VIEW FROM TNA! DEFINATELY WORTH $15 FROM BEST BUY. I HIGHLY RECOMMEND THIS DVD WITH BOUND FOR GLORY!P.S., GENESIS PAY PER VIEW WAS THE SAME NIGHT WHEN EDDIE GUERRERO PASSED AWAY :( AFTER THE SHOW TEAM 3D, RHINO, CHRISTIAN CAGE AND THE FANS ALL PAID TRIBUTE TO HIM. BROTHER RAY ALSO LAID OUT AN EDDIE GUERRERO SIGN IN THE MIDDLE OF THE RING PAYING TRIBUTE TO EDDIE. RIP! WE LOVE YOU EDDIE!

reviewText: Genesis took place on November 13th, 2005. After a full year of 3 hour ppvs being put on, TNA ended it's first year with a bang as Christain Cage arrived at TNA, a great card of matches took place, and the entire TNA company paid tribute to Eddie Guerrero who tragically passed away on the same day....Raven vs. PJ Polaco:This was during Raven's little fued with Larry Zybisco [I don't know how to spell his last name] Larry gave him two choices: leave TNA or fight a mystery opponent. Raven chose to stay and faced PJ Polaco, AKA Justin Credible. This was a good match, and Credible even smashed a kendo stick over Cassidy Riley's head as he protected Raven. Raven gets the win on Polaco. 7/10Hockey Stick MatchTeam Canada vs. 3LK [Kip James special guest referee]This was a brawl from start to finish. Watch BG James give a big back body drop to Bobby Roode onto the ramp and Konnan stick his shoe on a hockey stick and beat up Team Canada. Not much action with the sticks till near the end as both teams arm themselves with sticks and actually have a mini sword fight brawl. The end comes when Ron Killings lands a leg drop on a bunch of sticks right on top of Eric Young's family jewels. Good mid card match. 8/10#1 Contendership MatchJeff Hardy vs. Monty Brown:I always find Monty Brown's facial expressions funny during his matches, and watch his face contort as Jeff lands a leg drop onto his "Testicular" region. The match goes outside the ring and Jeff even jumps over a row or two of people and lands on Monty Brown outside the ring! Jeff put up a good fight, but The Pounce claimed another victim and Monty Brown won the match. 7.5/108 Man Tag Team Elimination MatchChristopher Daniels, Samoa Joe, Alex Shelley, and Roderick Strong vs. Chris Sabin, Sonjay Dutt, Matt Bently, and Austin Aries:This is just a fantastic wrestling match. One of the longer matches on the card and it did not dissapoint. Sonjay Dutt shows some intense high flying moves in this one [too bad about the slip up though] and Chris Sabin shows some true grit as he is left alone against Daniels and Joe near the end. However Daniels gets the pin on Sabin, winning the match for his team. 9/10[After the match Joe goes beserk and absolutely destroys Daniels with a steel chair because Daniels got the pinfall victory, not Joe]No Disqualification MatchSabu vs. Abyss:This is the second best of their one on one matches [In my opinion] Some great spots including: Sabu landing a leg drop onto Abyss through a table from the ring, Abyss giving huge chairshots to Sabu. Weapons included were: chairs, tables, thumbtacks, and a chair wrapped in barb wire. Abyss chokeslams Sabu onto the tacks, then misses a splash onto Sabu and lands chest first on tacks. In the end Sabu blocks a powerbomb on the barbed wire chair, but gets a black hole slam right onto it seconds later! Abyss wins the match. Good match but WAAAAY too short, should have been a few minutes longer 8.5/10[Watch the crowd reaction when they see Sabu's back for the first time after landing on the tacks, it's pretty entertaining.]X Division ChampionshipAJ Styles [Champion] vs. Petey Williams:Great match, better than the one they had in the same month the year before. Some fast paced moves and watch a german suplex onto the side of the barricade! Aj wins after giving the Styles Clash to Petey from the ropes for the win. 9.5/106 Man Tag Team MatchThe Dudley Boyz and Rhino vs. Jeff Jarrett and AMW:This was a massive brawl from start to finish. All 6 men literally fight all over the arena. Onto the ramps, into the crowd, on the announce tables, in the ring, by the entrance ways, on the stadium steps, everywhere except the back had some brawling going on.Highlights inlcude: Rhino falling down the entire stadium steps after Jeff Jarret shoved him off, Bubba Ray using a CHEESE GRATER on James Storms' head, Chris Harris hitting multiple chair shots onto Team 3D, Jeff Jarret getting smacked in the head with a trash can, Bubba Ray powerbombing Chris Harris onto the ground, and James Storm hitting a superkick onto Rhino as he tried to gore Jarrett through a table at the entranceway. Team 3D hit the 3D onto Harris for the win. 10/10 [Exciting Brawl all over the building.]After the match Christain Cage comes down to the ring and announces that he will not join Jeff Jarret's side and helps The Dudley Boyz give a 3D to Jeff Jarret through a table.Great PPV, one of my personal favorites for the last four matches alone. What makes TNA DVDS great are that they are a lot cheaper than normal DVDS, yet they are just as good if not better. This one is highly recommended......
summary: TNA's Genesis was indeed the beginning of a new year...
